1
00:00:00,385 --> 00:00:28,704
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhudassam Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhudassam Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhudassam

2
00:00:28,684 --> 00:00:33,308
homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-enlightened one.

3
00:00:37,652 --> 00:00:58,590
So now the next passage I want to read is the one where he tells us really about what constitutes his awakening or at least the main thrust of his awakening we can say

4
00:01:00,966 --> 00:01:07,114
Monks, before my enlightenment, while I was still a Bodhisattva, not yet fully enlightened, it occurred to me.

5
00:01:08,615 --> 00:01:22,573
Alas, this world has fallen into trouble, in that it is born, ages and dies, it passes away and is reborn, yet it does not understand the escape from this suffering, headed by aging and death.

6
00:01:24,635 --> 00:01:28,721
When now will an escape be discerned from this suffering, headed by aging and death?

7
00:01:29,242 --> 00:01:30,162
So this is...

8
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:32,171
an old theme, isn't it?

9
00:01:32,191 --> 00:01:41,766
This goes back really to that youthful time when he wakes up to the existential problems of life.

10
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:49,938
But this seems to, and this tells us that it was sort of on his mind really, even when he was becoming ascetic.

11
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:53,805
This is all before, you see, before he became liberated.

12
00:01:55,355 --> 00:02:00,180
And then it occurred to me, when what exists, does aging and death come to be?

13
00:02:00,661 --> 00:02:02,522
By what is aging and death conditioned?

14
00:02:04,405 --> 00:02:08,509
Then through careful attention, there took place in me a breakthrough by wisdom.

15
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:12,974
When there is birth, aging and death comes to be.

16
00:02:13,014 --> 00:02:18,221
And when aging and death has birth as its condition.

17
00:02:19,663 --> 00:02:21,884
It seems pretty obvious really, doesn't it?

18
00:02:23,737 --> 00:02:29,025
Because the scriptures make it a huge breakthrough.

19
00:02:29,064 --> 00:02:35,473
But he sort of says, well, what is the primary condition for aging and death?

20
00:02:35,493 --> 00:02:36,074
Well, it's birth.

21
00:02:36,495 --> 00:02:44,025
So we have to be a little patient because he now goes deeper, of course.

22
00:02:44,579 --> 00:02:45,840
So that was his first thought.

23
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:48,163
Well, you know, you've got to start from somewhere.

24
00:02:48,443 --> 00:02:51,727
So how is it I'm growing old and having to die, you see?

25
00:02:52,168 --> 00:02:53,149
Well, it's because I was born.

26
00:02:53,429 --> 00:02:54,449
That's pretty straightforward.

27
00:02:57,092 --> 00:03:11,650
Then, monks, it occurred to me, when what exists, does birth come to be, existence come to be, clinging, craving, feeling, contact, the six sense bases, name and form, by what is name and form conditioned?

28
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:17,463
Then through careful attention there took place in me a breakthrough by wisdom.

29
00:03:18,584 --> 00:03:21,967
When there is consciousness, name and form comes to be.

30
00:03:22,007 --> 00:03:25,490
Name and form has consciousness as its condition.

31
00:03:26,890 --> 00:03:30,033
So here we're running through dependence origination, usual stuff.

32
00:03:30,735 --> 00:03:33,217
So you can, these all refer back to themselves.

33
00:03:34,177 --> 00:03:42,884
You know, clinging is dependent on existence, craving dependent on clinging, feeling, it's sort of going back on itself, right?

34
00:03:44,332 --> 00:03:55,579
But then he comes to this point of consciousness, name and form.

35
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:58,566
Name and form is really the psychophysical organism.

36
00:04:00,370 --> 00:04:02,594
Remember that when he talks about form,

37
00:04:04,414 --> 00:04:10,923
at its most subtle level, it's the point where mind and matter meet.

38
00:04:13,406 --> 00:04:16,569
So in other words, we can't know a fingernail.

39
00:04:16,730 --> 00:04:18,473
You can't be in a fingernail.

40
00:04:19,293 --> 00:04:21,997
You can only know it by the sense of touch.

41
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:26,822
So that's at its more subtle level.

42
00:04:28,586 --> 00:04:31,249
So he's come now to this point about consciousness.

43
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:38,398
Then, monks, it occurred to me, when what exists does consciousness come to be?

44
00:04:39,939 --> 00:04:41,800
By what is consciousness conditioned?

45
00:04:42,901 --> 00:04:50,930
Then, monks, through careful attention, so this is the Vipassana, there took place in me a breakthrough of wisdom.

46
00:04:51,810 --> 00:04:55,295
When there is name-form, consciousness comes to be.

47
00:04:56,235 --> 00:04:58,737
Consciousness has name-form as its condition.

48
00:05:01,451 --> 00:05:06,098
So without the psychophysical organism there can't be consciousness, basically.

49
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:10,545
But then it occurred to me, this consciousness turns back.

50
00:05:12,127 --> 00:05:14,192
It does not go further than name form.

51
00:05:17,276 --> 00:05:22,845
It is to this extent that one may be born and age and die, pass away and be reborn.

52
00:05:22,884 --> 00:05:28,033
That is, when there is consciousness with name and form as its condition.

53
00:05:28,586 --> 00:05:31,769
and name and form with consciousness as its condition.

54
00:05:34,031 --> 00:05:51,307
When name and form is conditioned, the six sense bases, with the six sense bases as conditioned, contact and so on, the whole path of dependrigenation, such is the origin of the whole mass of suffering.

55
00:05:52,108 --> 00:05:57,091
So, he's taken us back to this point of consciousness

56
00:05:58,877 --> 00:06:05,625
Now that consciousness is disputed a little bit.

57
00:06:06,266 --> 00:06:07,447
It's an act of knowing.

58
00:06:07,487 --> 00:06:13,634
If there wasn't consciousness, there'd be just an automaton, wouldn't there?

59
00:06:13,653 --> 00:06:14,293
Just a machine.

60
00:06:16,377 --> 00:06:17,697
There's something that knows.

61
00:06:18,819 --> 00:06:25,386
But it can only know what it knows through the psychophysical organism.

62
00:06:25,406 --> 00:06:27,247
And the psychophysical organism

63
00:06:29,708 --> 00:06:31,589
is unknowable without consciousness.

64
00:06:39,276 --> 00:06:45,863
So if you took away the psychophysical organism how could consciousness of anything arise?

65
00:06:47,545 --> 00:06:55,192
If you took away consciousness how could the knowing, how could you know anything about the psychophysical organism?

66
00:06:55,213 --> 00:06:57,774
So these two rest against each other.

67
00:06:58,598 --> 00:07:00,600
the one arising completely dependent on the other.

68
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:04,245
That's where the origination starts and ends.

69
00:07:04,887 --> 00:07:05,889
You can't go beyond that.

70
00:07:06,288 --> 00:07:09,713
You can't go beyond the bubble of your consciousness.

71
00:07:11,997 --> 00:07:13,860
Basically what he's saying.

72
00:07:13,879 --> 00:07:17,105
You can't get outside the bubble of your consciousness.

73
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:27,079
And you can't get outside the bubble of your psychophysical organism.

74
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:27,980
That's it.

75
00:07:32,449 --> 00:07:32,870
Fancy.

76
00:07:36,757 --> 00:07:55,908
Then he says, Origination, origination, thus monks, in regard to things unheard before there arose in me, sorry, I'm reading that wrongly, origination, origination, thus monks, in regard to things unheard before

77
00:07:56,750 --> 00:08:24,934
there arose in me vision, knowledge, wisdom, penetration and light so these are just synonyms for enlightenment, awakening, understanding and then of course he goes back on it so now he's understood how we come to exist how we go through this process of becoming so now of course he goes back on that so when what does not exist does aging and death not come to be

78
00:08:25,824 --> 00:08:31,254
With the cessation of what does the cessation of aging and death come about?

79
00:08:31,274 --> 00:08:37,927
Then monks, through careful attention, there took place in me a breakthrough by wisdom, when there's no birth.

80
00:08:40,352 --> 00:08:47,866
Aging and death does not come to me, come to be, and with cessation of birth comes cessation of aging and death.

81
00:08:49,822 --> 00:08:53,730
So then, the process of cessation, right?

82
00:08:54,610 --> 00:09:00,582
Without the psychophysical organism, you can't have the sixth sense basis.

83
00:09:00,803 --> 00:09:08,860
You can't have contact, you can't have feeling, you can't have craving, so on, so on, so on.

84
00:09:08,879 --> 00:09:11,104
And then it occurred to me, when, what...

85
00:09:12,332 --> 00:09:15,056
does not exist, does consciousness come to be?

86
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:31,777
When what does not exist, does consciousness not come to be?

87
00:09:33,719 --> 00:09:38,424
With the cessation of what, does the cessation of consciousness come to be?

88
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:45,182
Then monks, through careful attention, there took place in me this breakthrough by wisdom.

89
00:09:45,202 --> 00:09:50,495
When there's no name and form, psychophysical organism, consciousness does not come to be.

90
00:09:51,096 --> 00:09:59,215
With the cessation of name and form comes the cessation of consciousness.

91
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:09,028
So now he says, this occurred to me, I have discovered this path to enlightenment.

92
00:10:09,429 --> 00:10:14,320
That is, with the cessation of name and form comes cessation of consciousness.

93
00:10:15,442 --> 00:10:19,068
With the cessation of consciousness comes the cessation of name and form.

94
00:10:20,071 --> 00:10:24,460
And with the cessation of name and form, there comes the cessation of the six bases.

95
00:10:26,481 --> 00:10:29,227
and through the six bases, contact, and so on and so forth.

96
00:10:29,989 --> 00:10:32,936
Such is the cessation of this whole mass of suffering.

97
00:10:36,682 --> 00:10:46,043
Cessation, cessation, thus monks, in regard to things unheard of before, there arose in me vision, knowledge, wisdom, penetration, and light.

98
00:10:47,879 --> 00:10:57,889
That's why here we chant this dependent origination because it's so core to his understanding of how everything happens and everything disappears.

99
00:10:59,775 --> 00:11:21,835
And because he saw that, he saw there was nothing in it that was substantial All this is not self, all this also doesn't have any substance to it And it's in constant motion, you're constantly turning that wheel, going through that process

100
00:11:28,918 --> 00:11:56,378
and then as usual he gives us an image suppose a man wandering through a forest would see an ancient path an ancient road traveled upon by people in the past he would follow it and would see an ancient city an ancient capital that had been inhabited by people in the past with parks and groves ponds and ramparts a delightful place then the man would inform the king or his royal minister sire

101
00:11:56,965 --> 00:12:03,534
Know that while wandering through the forest I saw an ancient path, an ancient road, travelled upon by people in the past.

102
00:12:04,015 --> 00:12:14,732
I followed it and saw an ancient city, an ancient capital that had been inhabited by people in the past, with parks, groves, ponds and ramparts, a delightful place.

103
00:12:14,753 --> 00:12:16,456
Renovate that city, sire.

104
00:12:16,996 --> 00:12:20,221
Then the king or the royal minister would renovate that city.

105
00:12:20,354 --> 00:12:28,601
And sometime later that city would become successful and prosperous, well populated, filled with people, attained to growth and expansion.

106
00:12:29,542 --> 00:12:37,850
So too, monks, I saw the ancient path, the ancient road travelled by the perfectly enlightened ones of the path.

107
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:40,732
And what is that ancient path, that ancient road?

108
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:47,778
It is just this noble eightfold path, that is, right view, right intention, right speech, right action,

109
00:12:48,096 --> 00:12:52,606
Right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness and right concentration.

110
00:12:53,188 --> 00:13:03,613
I followed that path and by doing so I have directly known aging and death, its origin, its cessation and the way leading to its cessation.

111
00:13:04,173 --> 00:13:07,100
And I've directly known birth and existence.

112
00:13:07,874 --> 00:13:09,917
I always prefer the word becoming, frankly.

113
00:13:10,738 --> 00:13:24,717
Clinging, craving, feeling, contact, the six sense bases, name and form, consciousness, volitional formations, that's your sankhara, their origin, their cessation, and the way leading to their cessation.

114
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:35,011
Having directly known them, I have explained them to the monks, to the nuns, to male lay followers and the female lay followers.

115
00:13:35,784 --> 00:13:47,418
this spiritual life, monks, has become successful and prosperous, extended, popular, widespread, well-proclaimed among the devas and humans.

116
00:13:50,062 --> 00:14:01,775
I can only hope that this little reading and small explanation will drive you swiftly along the road, travelling to Nibbana, sooner rather than later.

117
00:14:03,577 --> 00:14:07,918
Salute, salute, salute.

